org.tinfour.demo.utils

Class TabulatorDelta

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.tinfour.demo.utils.TabulatorDelta

  • public class TabulatorDelta
extends Object
    Tabulates mean and variance for "delta" values obtained from tests in which the result is found by comparing an estimated value (such as an interpolation result) with a known or expected value. The tabulator collects sums using both the signed values of the deltas as well as the absolute values of the deltas. The Kahan Summation algorithm is used to provide extended precision when processing a very large number of samples.

        public double getSumSignedValues()
        Gets the sum of the signed sample values as input into this tabulator. In practice, a sum with a large positive or negative value would mean that the process used to estimate values consistently overshot or undershot the actual value.
